	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Perspective</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">teaguecl wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">they consider the horizontal blanking period to be an the <strong>beginning</strong> of  a scanline instead of at the end.</div>
<br />The Atari 2600 console considers hblank to start a scanline as well. The GBA, on the other hand, follows the opposite convention, which causes no end of "what's the deal with the first scanline?" questions when newbies discover hblank DMA.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

